   "source": [
    "# Advanced evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial explains the evaluation metrics that are used in the spapros evaluation pipeline and exemplifies how the results can be visualized.\n",
    "\n",
    "The used dataset contains 3k PBMCs from a healthy donor and is publicly available from\n",
    "[10x Genomics](https://support.10xgenomics.com/single-cell-gene-expression/datasets/1.1.0/pbmc3k)\n",
    "[here](http://cf.10xgenomics.com/samples/cell-exp/1.1.0/pbmc3k/pbmc3k_filtered_gene_bc_matrices.tar.gz).\n",
    "\n",
    "You can also derive it from scanpy [here](https://scanpy.readthedocs.io/en/stable/generated/scanpy.datasets.pbmc3k.html#scanpy.datasets.pbmc3k), like we will do in this tutorial.\n",
    "\n",
    "The preprocessed Anndata consists of log-normalized single cell RNAseq counts of 2638 cells for 1838 genes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Content**  \n",
    "\n",
    "0. [Import packages and setup](#0.-Import-packages-and-setup)  \n",
    "1. [Load dataset](#1.-Load-dataset)  \n",
    "2. [Set up the ProbesetEvaluator](#2.-Set-up-the-ProbesetEvaluator)\n",
    "3. [Run evaluation methods](#3.-Run-evaluation-methods)\n",
    "4. [Visualize the evaluation results](#4.-Visualize-the-evaluation-results)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 0. Import packages and setup\n",
    "\n",
    "To run the notebook locally, create a conda environment using this [yaml file](../requirements_dev.yaml):\n",
    "\n",
    "    conda create -f environment.yaml\n",
    "\n",
    "Then add the conda environment as ipython kernel:\n",
    "\n",
    "    python -m ipykernel install --user --name spapros --display-name Python (spapros)\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "is_executing": true,
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import spapros\n",
    "from spapros import se, ev, pl\n",
    "from IPython.display import clear_output\n",
    "import scanpy as sc\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import yaml\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "pycharm": {
     "name": "#%%\n"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "scanpy==1.8.2 anndata==0.8.0 umap==0.5.2 numpy==1.21.5 scipy==1.7.3 pandas==1.3.5 scikit-learn==1.0.2 statsmodels==0.13.2 python-igraph==0.9.9 pynndescent==0.5.6\n",
      "spapros==0.1.0\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "sc.settings.verbosity = 0\n",
    "sc.logging.print_header()\n",
    "print(f\"spapros=={spapros.__version__}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "AnnData object with n_obs × n_vars = 2638 × 1838\n",
       "    obs: 'size_factors', 'celltype'\n",
       "    var: 'gene_ids', 'highly_variable', 'means', 'dispersions', 'dispersions_norm'\n",
       "    uns: 'hvg', 'log1p'"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "adata = sc.datasets.pbmc3k()\n",
    "adata_tmp = sc.datasets.pbmc3k_processed()\n",
    "adata = adata[adata_tmp.obs_names, adata_tmp.var_names]\n",
    "adata_raw = adata.copy()\n",
    "sc.pp.normalize_total(adata, target_sum=1e4, key_added=\"size_factors\")\n",
    "sc.pp.highly_variable_genes(adata, flavor=\"cell_ranger\", n_top_genes=1000)\n",
    "adata.X = adata_raw.X\n",
    "sc.pp.log1p(adata)\n",
    "adata.obs['celltype'] = adata_tmp.obs['louvain']\n",
    "adata"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Set up the ProbesetEvaluator"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The quality of a selected probeset is not easy to describe. A useful probeset represents both the biological importance and the variability inherent in the total gene set. Spapros provides a set of evaluation metrics that measure the performance in these categories.\n",
    "\n",
    "By default, `metric_scheme=\"quick\"`, which means that only the faster metrics are calculated, which are:\n",
    "\n",
    ">- knn\n",
    ">- forest classification\n",
    ">- marker correlation (if marker list given: `marker_list=\"../path/to/marker_list.csv\"`)\n",
    ">- gene correlation\n",
    "\n",
    "Through setting scheme=\"full\", additionally the following metric is calculated:\n",
    ">- nmi\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Alternatively, you can specify `scheme=\"custom\"` and `metrics=custom_list` where `custom_list` is a list of the metrics of interest.\n",
    "\n",
    "Below, the metrics will be further explained."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For each evaluation metric, several parameters can be customized. Therefor, the ProbesetEvaluator takes an dictionary containing the parameters as values as `metric_params` argument.\n",
    "Here, we stored a set of paramets in a yaml file:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'data': {'name': 'adata_pbmc3k', 'celltype_key': 'celltype'},\n",
       " 'metrics': {'cluster_similarity': {'ns': [5, 21],\n",
       "   'AUC_borders': [[7, 14], [15, 20]]},\n",
       "  'knn_overlap': {'ks': [5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30]},\n",
       "  'forest_clfs': {'ct_key': 'celltype', 'threshold': 0.8},\n",
       "  'marker_corr': {'per_celltype': True,\n",
       "   'per_marker': True,\n",
       "   'per_celltype_min_mean': None,\n",
       "   'per_marker_min_mean': 0.025},\n",
       "  'gene_corr': {'threshold': 0.8}}}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 5,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# loading metric parameters from file\n",
    "param_yaml = \"../tutorials/data/pbmc3k_parameters.yml\"\n",
    "with open(param_yaml, \"r\") as file:\n",
    "    custom_params = yaml.load(file, Loader=yaml.FullLoader)\n",
    "custom_params"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# initialize an ProbesetEvaluator\n",
    "evaluator = ev.ProbesetEvaluator(adata,\n",
    "#                                  metrics_params=custom_params,\n",
    "                                 scheme=\"full\",\n",
    "                                 marker_list=\"../data/pbmc3k_marker_list.csv\",\n",
    "                                 verbosity=2,\n",
    "                                 results_dir=None)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3.  Run evaluation methods"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The principal method for evaluation is `ProbesetEvaluator.evaluate_probeset()`, which needs to be invoked once for each probe set.\n",
    "All results are stored as class variables.\n",
    "The `set_id` has to be specified in each iteration. Otherwise, the results will be overwritten."
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "I this plot, each row summarizes the evaluation metrics of one probeset.\n",
    "The metrics evaluating the variability recovery are shown in the green columns (1-3).\n",
    "In the first column, you can see the NMI of coarse clusterings of the selected probe set and the full gene set.\n",
    "Here, for both gene sets clusters with between 5 and 20 clusters were created.\n",
    "The second column shows the NMI of clusterings from 21 to 60 clusters and thus represents the performance of finer variability recovery.\n",
    "As the clusterings should picture the heterogeinity of the expression data, a variability recovering subset would would cluster similarly.\n",
    "Both NMI values are highest for the pca based selection, which indicates that this method recovers the variability best.\n",
    "\n",
    "The third column reveals the graph overlap of the knn graphs of the full gene set and the respective probeset. If this value is high, it means that fine variations within the full gene set are captured by the probeset.\n",
    "\n",
    "The subsequent purple columns (4-8) indicate the performance of each selection method with respect to cell type identification.\n",
    "Column 4 contains the mean classification accuracy of a random forest prediction over cell types. This quantifies the overall classification success while column 5 provides an estimate for the percentage of reliably captured cell types, i.e. the average of a smoothed thresholding of classification performance around 0.8 for each cell type.\n",
    "The other 3 purple columns (6-8) derive from the comparison of the correlation within the selected probeset with the correlation within the marker list.\n",
    "\n",
    "The last two, blue columns (9, 10) evaluate the correlation within a selected probeset. If genes with highly correlated expression are selected, the information content could also be provided by just one of them.\n"
   ]
  },
